question_text:
A multi-step chemical synthesis is described below.

Initial compound:
CC2=c1cccc1C3(C)COC(=O)C23C

Step 1 conditions:
m) MeMgBr;
then NEt3, MsCl;
then n) NIS, BnOH, −78 °C;
then o) KF, 100 °C;
then p) Boc-NHOH, DMP

Step 2 conditions:
q) Pd(OH)2/C, H2;
then r) Mo(CO)6, MeCN/H2O, 100 °C

Step 3 conditions:
s) TFA;
then t) Na2WO4, H2O2;
then u) TiCl3-HCl

Step 4 conditions:
v) MeLi, LaCl3•2LiCl;
then w) RuCl3, NaIO4;
then x) Pd(OH)2/C, H2

Task:
Determine the ordered sequence of reaction products (in SMILES format)
formed after each step of the synthesis.
Provide the SMILES separated by commas in the correct order.

A multi-step chemical synthesis is described below.

Initial compound:
COc1ccc(C=O)cc1O

Step 1 conditions:
1) MOMCl, DIPEA, DCM, 0°C to rt;
2) CSA, HC(OMe)3, MeOH, 0°C;
3) n-BuLi, Et2O, 0°C, I2, THF

Step 2 conditions:
1) AcOH, THF/H2O, 0°C to rt;
2) MeOCH2PPh3Cl, NaHMDS, THF, 0°C to rt;
3) AcOH, MeOH, 40°C

Step 3 conditions:
CC(C)(C)[Si](C)(C)OCC1=CCCC2OC12,
Pd2(dba)3, P(2-furyl)3, MeCN, rt

Step 4 conditions:
1) p-nitrobenzoic acid, DEAD, PPh3, toluene/THF, 0°C to rt;
2) CSA, MeOH, rt

Step 5 conditions:
1) CC(C)(O)C#N, DEAD, PPh3, toluene, 0°C to rt;
2) LiBH4, Et2O/MeOH, 0°C to rt;
3) TBSCl, Im, DMF, rt

Step 6 conditions:
1) DIBAL, DCM, −78°C;
2) NaBH4, MeOH, −78°C to rt;
3) ClCO2Me, K2CO3

Step 7 conditions:
Pd2(dba)3, P(o-tolyl)3, NEt3, MeCN;
then TBAF, THF, rt (Heck coupling)

Step 8 conditions:
HCl, MeOH, reflux (Mannich-type reaction)

Step 9 conditions:
1) TMSCl, LHDMS, THF, 0°C;
2) Pd(OAc)2, MeCN, rt (Ito–Saegusa oxidation)

Step 10 conditions:
1) aq. H2O2, NaOH, MeCN, 0°C;
2) NaBH4, MeOH/DCM;
3) TCDI, DMAP, DCE, 60°C;
4) BEt3, n-Bu3SnH, THF

Step 11 conditions:
1) DMP, DCM, rt;
2) LAH, THF, reflux

Step 12 conditions:
BBr3, DCM, rt

Task:
Determine the ordered sequence of reaction products (in SMILES format)
formed after each step of the synthesis.
Provide the SMILES separated by commas in the correct order.
